15/12/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Political consultations with Russia are scheduled on Monday (15 December) at the foreign ministry. 
The talks will be led by Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Vladimir Chizhov and Bulgarian Deputy Ministers Lyubomir Ivanov and Katya Todorova. 
The topics include issues related to Bulgaria's upcoming chairmanship-in-office of the OSCE. 
The sides will also discuss bilateral relations and opportunities for enhancement.
In other news, a Bulgarian delegation visited Algeria at the weekend and discussed establishment of a joint business council. 
The two countries' Chambers of Commerce signed a co-operation agreement. 
(BTA, Trud, 24 Chassa - 15/12/03; BNT - 14/12/03)
